<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <title>Body</title>

</head>

<body>
    <div class="container-fluid ">
        <h3 class=" section-top-title">General UI Element</h3>
        <div class="section-top-subtitle">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-6">
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <h2>Contextual Label Classes</h2>
                        <p>Label renamed to badges.</p>
                       
                        <h2>Pill Badges</h2>
                        <span class="badge badge-pill badge-primary">Primary</span>
                        <span class="badge badge-pill badge-secondary">Secondary</span>
                        <span class="badge badge-pill badge-success">Success</span>
                        <span class="badge badge-pill badge-danger">Danger</span>
                        <span class="badge badge-pill badge-warning">Warning</span>
                        <span class="badge badge-pill badge-info">Info</span>
                        <span class="badge badge-pill badge-light">Light</span>
                        <span class="badge badge-pill badge-dark">Dark</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-6">
                    <div class="form-group ">
                        <h2>Contextual Badges Classes</h2>
                        <p>Contextual classes can be used to color the Badges.</p>
                        <a href="#">News
                            <span class="badge ">5</span>
                        </a>&nbsp;
                        <a href="#">Comments
                            <span class="badge">10</span>
                        </a>&nbsp;
                        <a href="#">Updates
                            <span class="badge">2</span>
                        </a>
                        <h2>Badges on Buttons</h2>
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Primary
                            <span class="badge">7</span>
                        </button>
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-success">Success
                            <span class="badge">3</span>
                        </button>
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Danger
                            <span class="badge">5</span>
                        </button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
            <div class="container ">
                <h2>Contextual Colors</h2>
                <p>Use the contextual classes to provide "meaning through colors":</p>
                <p class="text-muted">This text is muted.</p>
                <p class="text-primary">This text is important.</p>
                <p class="text-success">This text indicates success.</p>
                <p class="text-info">This text represents some information.</p>
                <p class="text-warning">This text represents a warning.</p>
                <p class="text-danger">This text represents danger.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
            <div class="col">
                <h1>Blockquotes</h1>
                <p>The blockquote element is used to present content from another source:</p>
                <blockquote>
                    <p>For 50 years, WWF has been protecting the future of nature. The world's leading conservation
                        organization,
                        WWF works in 100 countries and is supported by 1.2 million members in the United States and
                        close
                        to 5 million globally.</p>
                    <footer>From WWF's website</footer>
                </blockquote>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
            <div class="col shade2">
                <h1>Blockquotes</h1>
                <p>To show the quote on the right use the class .blockquote-reverse:</p>
                <blockquote class="blockquote-reverse">
                    <p>For 50 years, WWF has been protecting the future of nature. The world's leading conservation
                        organization, WWF works in 100 countries and is supported by 1.2 million members in the United
                        States and close to 5 million globally.</p>
                    <footer>From WWF's website</footer>
                </blockquote>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</body>

</html>